header.gameNote: NIT SEASON TIP-OFF AT SPOKANE WA

article.headline: Baylor 87, Colorado State 82 (2OT)
article.story: SPOKANE, Wash. (AP) -- Henry Dugat scored 29 points as Baylor beat Colorado State 87-82 in double overtime on Tuesday in the opening game of the NIT Season Tip-Off at the Spokane Arena. Two free-throws by Tim Bush with 41 seconds left provided the winning points for Baylor (2-0). Jason Smith scored 25 points and grabbed 19 rebounds for Colorado State (1-1). In the second overtime, Dugat's basket with 3 minutes left lifted Baylor to a 79-78 lead. After a Colorado State turnover, Aaron Bruce's runner made it 81-78 Baylor with 2:27 left. Smith's layup cut Baylor's lead to 81-80. Stuart Creason's short jumper gave the Rams an 82-81 lead with 59 seconds left. Bush was fouled and made both free-throws to lift Baylor to an 83-82 lead with 41 seconds left. Colorado State turned the ball over and was forced to foul with 16 seconds remaining. Duget made two free-throws with 16 seconds left for an 85-82 Baylor. Cory Lewis' 3-point shot fell short for Colorado State. In the first overtime, Dugat's runner with 45 seconds left gave Baylor a 75-73 lead. But Smith's layup with 18 seconds left tied the score. Curtis Jerrells missed an open 3-pointer at the buzzer to send the game into a second overtime. Near the end of regulation time, free-throws by Tim Denson and Smith built a 66-61 CSU lead. Dugat's 3-pointer with 1:52 left and his short jumper with 45 seconds left tied the score at 66-66. Both teams missed shots as regulation ended. Baylor went on an early 14-1 run to take a 23-7 lead in the first-half, and led 29-28 at halftime. On Wednesday, Baylor will play Gonzaga which beat Rice 88-50. CSU will play Rice.
